definition.value: A compound that inhibits the growth of marine organisms.
A sophorolipid that is the diacetylated sophoroside of 13-hydroxydocosanoic acid. It is a major extracellular lipid.
A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine substituted by a methylsulfanyl group at position 6 and a tert-buty group at the amino nitrogen atom.
Any member of the class of nitrates resulting from the esterification of nitric acid with an alcohol.
A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a chemical context.
A group that is introduced into a molecule by chemical modification of a functional group in order to obtain chemoselectivity in a subsequent chemical reaction.
An organosilyl group consisting of three methyl groups bonded to a silicon atom with a free valence on silicon for bonding to the rest of a molecule.

A group, usually derived from the compound 4-toluenesulfonyl chloride, which forms esters and amides of toluenesulfonic acid; often used as a protecting group for alcohols and amines in organic synthesis reactions.
Groups containing a sulfur atom doubly-bonded to two oxygen atoms.
A sulfonyl group having 4-nitrophenyl as the S-substituent.
A compound that contains a 4,4-difluoro-4-bora-3a,4a-diaza-s-indacene skeleton.
A copper sulfide in which the metal is in the +2 oxidation state.
Compounds with the general formula CuxSy.
A copper sulfide in which the metal is in the +1 oxidation state.
